title: @OspreyVB Falls 3-1 to FGCU
text: recorded 21 digs. UNF hit .149 for the match, with 48 kills, 65 digs and 9.5 total team blocks. Eleonora Kazarian paced FGCU with 16 kills. Maggie Rick tallied a 40-assist, 10-dig double-double, while Vanessa Benke notched 22 digs. FGCU hit .119 for the match. The Eagles had 50 kills, 64 digs and 14.0 total team blocks. UNF battled back after a slow start to the first set. The Ospreys trailed by as many as seven points late in the set with FGCU taking a 20-13 lead on a UNF ball handling error. A kill from Desaulnay sparked a critical five-point run that pulled UNF to within two. UNF continued to fight back and tied the set at 23-23 on an Eagle blocking error. After trading points, FGCU captured the last two points it needed, which included a set-ending block from Marlena Moeller and Kazarian. The Ospreys were unable to overcome multiple runs by FGCU in the second set. With the Eagles up by four, FGCU pulled away from the Ospreys behind an eight-point run and went up 18-6 in the set. Although, UNF attempted to fight back, FGCU gained the set-point on an Osprey serving error in order to go up 2-0 in the match. UNF bounced back in the third set, leading the entire way.
